  "texts": [
    "Several strategies can be considered to guard against data poisoning, including validating and preprocessing training data, using outlier detection algorithms to flag suspicious information, and employing adversarial training programs that intentionally introduce spurious examples to train models to distinguish between authentic and deceptive inputs.",
    "A second security concern centers on data privacy-an especially pressing issue when it comes to personal health information.",
    "Even absent malicious intent, user privacy can be compromised.",
    "For example, a recent data breach at OpenAI's ChatGPT resulted in some users being able to see the titles of other people's conversations and contributed to Italy's decision to temporarily ban the product.",
    "Research has also demonstrated that adversarial attacks can recover individuals' information from LLMs, including names, phone numbers, and email addresses, even when models are trained on private datasets."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}